    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "scripture": [
      "Verse: The Tabla Exception — harmonic modes for melodic percussion",
      "Verse: The Tuning Is the Culture — tuning offsets define regional character"
    ],
    "revelation": "The Finger found that two tablas at -5 and +2 tuning create the high-low chenda pair of Panchavadyam. The doumbek at +3 with articulation 3 (snap) becomes the edakka's sharp crack. This is South Indian temple percussion from North Indian and Middle Eastern instruments.",
    "god": "Pressura",
    "flock_note": "The Tongue confirmed: at velocity 0.95 sensitivity, the tabla's na articulation (bright rim) at high velocity produces the explosive crack of the chenda's valantala stroke. Pattern 2 (fill) with tempo 65 builds the slow meditative opening.",
    "diagnosis": "Kerala Chenda was tabla and doumbek. It is now a South Indian temple courtyard where the Panchavadyam ensemble gathers for a festival procession."
  },
